<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9938206819288></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9938206819288><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9938206819288>How to leave the world of Norrath (not like anyone here woul</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9938206819288#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 29th 9:18 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well ive been eqless for a month now and i still havent gotten over it. If anyone here wants to know how to do it here it is. First you have to have a reason to stop. Personally it was taking up my whole life. Between eating, dumping, and sleeping (barely) there was EQ. The gift from the Gods i thought. Even if i wasnt playing then I was looking at all the cool characters on ebay or looking for new weapons i wanted or looking at this board right here. I knew it was time to quit when i did that reality check of /played. In the short 2 yrs that ive had the game i played 5 months. Almost a quarter of my life. Then i knew it was time to go. Well to do this is hard but you gotta log on and click the cancel account. Do it without thinking and just click it. Then uninstall EQ. Finally pray that u never go back. That is only if u really want to quit. I still find myself addicted. I still read about the ebay characters and look here every now and then. But if u want to quit then just do it without thinking. NEVER LOOK BACK. If u do ur screwed. Well goodbye all u EQ addicts, departing from Norrath is ever so hard. It will always be a part of me. Still wishing i was playing everquest or as some call it evercrack.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
