	   <tr><td colspan=2>First and foremost, you have to come to a realization in life that if you ain't a troll you really should be one.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you have resolved this satisfactorily in your mind, then you can move on to lesser issues such as what class to play.  Being a shaman, or rather being a Troll shaman-- actually to be completely accurate, the King of the Trolls who happens to be a shaman on the side, I can say with irrefutable authority that being a stinky, butt scratching, vile, foul mouthed, and violent Troll who loves to loll around in his own vomitus, there is no better race/class combination in the game.<br><br>"Oh, really?", you exclaim.  "Whatever.", you think. <br>Put your bigotry aside and see a life of freedom for what it is-- no more being nicey-nice to obnoxious people who pester you for SoWs and buffs.  No more being patient with idiot group members who can't handle the intricacies of group dynamics.  No more longsuffering tolerance of individuals who think they know how to run your character better than you.<br>You can reek havoc on their tiny little pinheads all the while blasting them with some well timed verbal assaults because YOU ARE A TROLL.  Noone expects you to be a good guy!  If you wanted to be sweet and lovable you should have chosen an effeminate elf paladin prancing and dancing your way through the woods spreading cheer and sunshine where 'er you go.<br>Let me say this one more time so as to leave no confusion in your lumpy question filled heads:  YOU__ARE__A__TROLL.<br><br>So go ahead, Mr. Trollman, be mean.  Be nasty.  Be obnoxious.  And don't forget to be witty while you're doing it-- your groupmates not on the receiving end of your bile will find it hilarious.  Hey, it's always funny when it happens to somebody else...<br><br>--Pusbag Infection, King of the Trolls<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
